# 11. ジャングルジムと流星群

Miku: I wonder when will Ichika and Saki come back?
Luka: Hehe. You're impatient to see them, aren't you?
Miku: Luka! I didn't notice you were there.
Luka: I've been watching you milling around restlessly.
Miku: Well, you should have said something instead of spying on me...
Luka: I, too, hope that they discover their true feelings soon.
Miku: Yeah. But I'm afraid they're not ready to face them yet.
Miku: Maybe here they can find the courage.
Luka: I hope so. Oh? I hear two pairs of footsteps running towards us.
Saki: Miku! Luka! Sorry for barging in! We have to master this song so that Shiho will join our band!
Ichika: I'm sorry if we're asking too much, but this is our chance to have Shiho join! Could you please help us practice?
Miku: Hehe. So your friend is considering joining your band after all?
Miku: You can always count on our help!
Miku: That phrasing was really good. Can we try it again?
Ichika: Okay. Once again from the top!
Saki: Luka, I don't know what sort of vibe this melody should have. What do you think?
Luka: Hmm... How about playing it this way?
Ichika: Oh, when did it get so late?
Saki: Is it late? Gosh, you're right! I was so absorbed, I didn't notice the time.
Ichika: It's always sunset in this world, so it feels as if time is standing still.
Miku: The scenery is also formed from your feelings. That's why it's that melancholy, lonesome time of the day here.
Ichika: Huh?
Saki: Say, isn't this song kinda difficult? You can tell Shiho chose it.
Luka: But don't you think she picked it because she really hopes you'll take this whole band thing seriously?
Saki: Yeah, I get that feeling too! And the more I play it, the more confident I get!
Saki: On a different note... Ichi, I came up with this tune while we were practicing. Want to hear it?
Ichika: An original tune? Sure.
Saki: Really? Yay! I'll play it now!
Saki: That's it...
Ichika: Huh, that's really neat.
Saki: You think so? Yay! You used to write song lyrics at one point, remember? Since then I've been composing little bits in my head every now and then!
Ichika: Ah, yeah. I had that phase, but I stopped writing a while back. But, I'll be happy to listen to any of your creations!
Saki: Thanks! By the way, did you notice this?
Ichika: This is a...star map?
Saki: Yeah. There's another one drawn on the blackboard, as if the class was preparing for a stargazing trip!
Saki: I'd love to go stargazing myself.
Miku: You can, if you go to the rooftop.
Saki: But it's still early in the evening...
Miku: SEKAI is a world created from your feelings. Give it a try.
Saki: Wow! Look at that! I don't think I've ever seen the night sky so clear!
Ichika: But how is this possible? The sun was setting only a moment ago!
Luka: This SEKAI was born from your thoughts and feelings, so the form it takes is based on that, too.
Ichika: Our feelings, huh...
Ichika: Saki, do you remember when all four of us were stargazing together?
Saki: Yeah, I do! We climbed the jungle gym and looked out for shooting stars!
Saki: Which constellation was it over? Cancer?
Ichika: Leo. We were watching the Leonids.
Saki: Right, right. That one. Hona tried so hard to teach us, remember?
Ichika: Yeah, she's always been interested in them.
Saki: But Shiho said none of Honami's lectures stuck in her mind. Not that I can really remember which is which, either.
Ichika: Hehe. I do, though. Honami repeated the names over and over, and she actually got upset with Shiho for not remembering any of them.
Saki: Oh yeah! Shiho and I weren't prepared for Honami's angry side, so we panicked and for once paid attention to the star map. I can't believe it was so long ago!
Ichika: Well... In a few days we're meeting up with Shiho.
Saki: We have to play that song perfectly, so that she'll join us!
Ichika: Maybe one day we'll all stargaze together again.
Saki: I hope so!
Ichika: (With Saki beside me, I'm hopeful that we can all be together again, just like before.)
Ichika: (I really want to be friends with Shiho again. I'll put everything I've got into playing that song.)
Ichika: We can do this, Saki.
Saki: Shiho, we're ready!
Shiho: I don't think this needs explaining, but if you mess up even just a bit, you can forget about me joining you.
Ichika: We're aware of that.
Shiho: Good. Let's head over to the studio.
Honami: (Isn't that...Shiho? She's with Saki and Ichika?)
Honami: (I wonder where they're going. Maybe they patched things up.)
Honami: .....
Honami's Classmate A: What's the hold up, Honami?
Honami: Oh, sorry! I'm coming!
Honami: (I'm happy for them, if they really made up. It's nice that they can be friends again.)
Honami: (It's for the best...)
Honami: (But why did seeing them together make me feel so lonely?)
